            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-04-07T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-04-07T19:00:00-05:00" n="641" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d641">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Council/4–747: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smith</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-04-07T19:00:00-05:00">April 7, 1947—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>836. <hi rend="smallcaps">Moskco</hi> 46. From Vincent for Carter. We do not
                    intend to initiate public announcement re sale of ammunition to China (ref <hi rend="smallcaps">Kosmos</hi> 22<note n="74" xml:id="d641fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note>) and will discourage publicity from
                    other sources. If <pb facs="0828" n="818" xml:id="pg_818"/> press obtain info
                    upon which to base inquiries, we would state that ammunition was procured for
                    Chinese as result of commitment made before V–J Day; that it is unsuitable for
                    use by US armed forces or sale elsewhere; that its retention is source of
                    expense to US Govt; and that therefore it is being declared surplus and sold to
                    China. If question of policy is received we would point out that transaction is
                    unrelated to and has no bearing upon general policy toward China as enunciated
                    in President’s statement of Dec 18, 1946,<note n="75" xml:id="d641fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">United States Relations With China</hi>, p. 689.</note>
                    supplemented in personal statement of Gen Marshall on Jan 7<note n="76" xml:id="d641fn3">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 686.</note> last. [Vincent.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
